question: Determine the year an iconic American television sitcom premiered, then using only historical corporate founding records from that year prior to October, identify the pioneering e-commerce entity established as an online bookstore that evolved into a transformative digital retail platform; using the referenced entity, determine the year's highest-selling fiction work published by an author born in a rural American community, then identify the single most revered cultural institution originating prior to 1900 that remains the defining annual gathering of the author's home state with continuous operation since the nineteenth century.
subject: web_search
derived_ev: The TV show Friends first aired in 1994
Amazon.com was founded by Jeff Bezos in July 1994 as an online bookstore and later became a pioneering e-commerce giant that transformed digital retail
The historically significant technology company founded in the same year Friends first aired is Amazon

Robert James Waller's *The Bridges of Madison County* was the #1 bestselling fiction title of 1994 with over 6 million copies sold by year-end, published by Warner Books months before Amazon's founding
Robert James Waller, author of *The Bridges of Madison County*, was born in Rockford, Iowa
Rockford, Iowa has a population of 600 and is embedded in Iowa's agricultural heartland where the Iowa State Fair—established in 1854—is the state's most revered cultural institution

The most iconic cultural tradition in Iowa that shaped Robert James Waller's upbringing environment and serves as the historically significant connection to the era when Amazon was founded is the Iowa State Fair
